# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Trivy vulnerability ignore list.
#
# Every entry here is a known deviation from the pipeline's fail-on-
# CRITICAL/HIGH stance in .github/workflows/ci.yml. Each entry MUST carry:
#   - the CVE ID
#   - a reason (why we cannot fix it right now)
#   - an `exp:` date (Trivy resumes flagging after this date)
#
# Before adding an entry, exhaust the alternatives in order:
#   1. Bump the base image digest in Dockerfile (Dependabot PR)
#   2. Bump the affected Python dependency in pyproject.toml + uv.lock
#   3. Patch the Dockerfile (only if 1 and 2 are unavailable)
# Ignoring a CVE is the last resort.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2026-28390 — OpenSSL: DoS via NULL pointer dereference in CMS (HIGH).
# Affects the Debian packages libssl3t64, openssl, openssl-provider-legacy
# (one source package, three binaries — Trivy reports it three times).
# Fixed upstream in Debian trixie as 3.5.5-1~deb13u2, but the Docker Library
# has not yet rebuilt python:3.12.x-slim to pick up the patch. Verified
# 2026-04-16: python:3.12-slim and python:3.12.13-slim both resolve to
# digest sha256:804ddf3251a60bbf9c92e73b7566c40428d54d0e79d3428194edf40da6521286
# and both still ship libssl3t64 3.5.5-1~deb13u1.
# Action: remove this entry once Dependabot opens a base image bump PR
# against the new digest. The `exp:` date forces re-evaluation.
CVE-2026-28390 exp:2026-05-31

# CVE-2026-31789 (CRITICAL), CVE-2026-28387 / CVE-2026-28388 / CVE-2026-28389
# (HIGH) — OpenSSL CVEs disclosed in the same advisory window, affecting the
# same Debian packages (libssl3t64, openssl, openssl-provider-legacy). Fixed
# upstream in Debian trixie as 3.5.5-1~deb13u2; same root cause as the
# CVE-2026-28390 entry above — python:3.12.x-slim has not yet been rebuilt
# against the patched Debian point release.
# Action: remove these entries once Dependabot opens a base image bump PR.
CVE-2026-31789 exp:2026-06-05
CVE-2026-28387 exp:2026-06-05
CVE-2026-28388 exp:2026-06-05
CVE-2026-28389 exp:2026-06-05
